{
  "texts": [
    "Participants also found them to be lacking in efficiency (P5, P10), usability (P5, P8, P9, P17), ill-supporting the effectiveness of visualization \"cannot handle many samples\", \"cannot sort\", (P5, P7, P10, P17), and intuitiveness or learnability (P5, P10, P15, P17, P20).",
    "For example, P5 said: \"Using IGV has cost me a significant amount of time to navigate back and forth for different reference genomes.\".",
    "Also, P20 stated \"It [the genome browser's design] is not done in a very beginner-friendly way.",
    "It's simple, but not intuitive.",
    "\"Regarding code editors, learnability was often found to be an issue in the authoring process."
  ]
}